parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission shifting issues can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission shifts harshly
hesitates
or slips between gears
causing the vehicle to jerk or lunge forward. The problem is often intermittent and unpredictable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and hard shifting can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or jerk, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates before shifting
causing the vehicle to lose power or hesitate. The transmission then shifts harshly
causing the vehicle to jerk or lunge forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to become undrivable, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage or disengage
causing the vehicle to become undrivable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coils can cause the engine to stall or misfire, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or misfires
the check engine light illuminates
the vehicle loses power
and the engine shakes or vibrates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to fail emissions tests, and in severe cases, can lead to carbon monoxide poisoning.
symptoms: The check engine light illuminates
the vehicle fails emissions tests
and there is a strong odor of sulfur or rotten eggs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PCV hose can cause the engine to stall or misfire, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or misfires
the check engine light illuminates
and there is a vacuum leak.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The gears slip or hesitate
the vehicle lurches forward
and the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coils can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the check engine light illuminates
the vehicle jerks or hesitates while accelerating
the vehicle has a rough idle
and there is an odor of gasoline.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Moisture ingress into the ignition coils can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving in wet conditions.
symptoms: The vehicle will not go over 40 mph
the vehicle thinks it is overheating and will not move
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor.
